                <h1>Understanding Delaware Background Check Laws</h1>
                <p>Delaware background check laws govern the process of screening individuals for criminal history, employment, and tenant qualifications. Employers must obtain written consent before running a check. The law requires that individuals be informed of any adverse decisions based on the results, ensuring transparency and fairness.</p>
